tion of the [[J. Paul Getty Museum]], Los Angeles. The Getty presented the first monographic exhibition of Ercole's work in 1999.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Jaff\u00e9|first=David |display-authors=etal |date=1999|title=Ercole De' Roberti The Renaissance in Ferrara|journal=The Burlington Magazine|volume=141 |issue=1153|pages=i\u2013xl|jstor=888299 }}</ref> At The [[Thyssen-Bornemisza Museum]] in Madrid there is a small panel from a ''cassone'' or wedding chest attributed to him. From around 1480 it narrates an episode of [[Ovid]]'s famous Metamorphoses, ''The argonauts leaving Colchis''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.museothyssen.org/en/collection/artists/roberti-ercole/argonauts-leaving-colchis|title=The Argonauts Leaving Colchis|website=Museo Nacional Thyssen-Bornemisza|language=en|access-date=24 april 2020}}</ref>\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n*[http://www.getty.edu/art/collection/artists/3323/ercole-de'roberti-italian-about-1450-1496/ The J. Paul Getty Museum: Ercole de' Roberti]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20090222203132/http://efn.org/~acd/vite/VasariErcole.html Vasari, ''Vite'', profile of Ercole]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20081122094217/http://www.liverpoolmuseums.org.uk/walker/collections/13c-16c/pieta.aspx 'Pieta' at the Walker Art Gallery, Liverpool, UK]\n*[http://www.getty.edu/art/gettyguide/artObjectDetails?artobj=1066 Information on ''St. Jerome in the Wilderness''], J. Paul Getty Museum, Los Angeles.\n*[https://www.nga.gov/collection/artist-info.1833.html Ercole de' Roberti at the National Gallery of Art] \n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Roberti, Ercole de'}}\n[[Category:1450s births]]\n[[Category:1496 deaths]]\n[[Category:People from Ferrara]]\n[[Category:15th-century Italian painters]]\n[[Category:Italian male painters]]\n[[Category:Ferrarese painters]]\n[[Category:Italian Renaissance painters]]\n", "name_user": "FydelJ", "label": "safe", "comment": "style correction", "url_page": "//en.wiki